Attempt 8 was interrupted by outer termination; **all of its uncommitted work was preserved, inspected, and re-verified** (nothing discarded), then completed in this attempt.

Resolved: **QA-263-014** (browser journey now completes the real F5 wizard handoff — explicit allergy state, #235 therapy + demographics acceptance, blocking checklist cleared, StepVerifica creation with explicit duplicate path — and asserts persistence via the backend `/patients` API **and** the UI after a full SPA reload, keeping the hard-failure regression path; reproduced root cause fixed: the #244 allergy-status selector was dead in intake mode — StepClinica now wires `status`/`onStatusChange` and IntakeWorkspace carries `allergieStatus` into `cartella.allergieStatus`) and **QA-263-015** (claims may only name a **registered** `git worktree list` root — nested paths that pass branch/origin checks by upward resolution are rejected; a read-only `resolveIssueWorktree` runs before the claim and the runtime verifies prepared == claimed and runs Claude in exactly the claimed cwd; a lease heartbeat refreshes the GitHub claim during the whole Claude execution and a failed refresh aborts the owned process tree through the runner's new AbortSignal support; an owned-children registry + `killOwnedProcessTrees()` + process exit hook guarantee supervisor termination leaves no orphan, and a lost lease restores `ready-for-dev` + `assigned-to-claude` deterministically).

